    bodyHtml: "<p>Switching from another EOS tool? OrgTP imports your data.</p>\n<p><strong>Where:</strong> <code>/import/ninety</code> (for Ninety.io) or <code>/import/bloom</code> (for Bloom Growth). Both work identically.</p>\n<ol><li>In your old tool, export your <strong>Rocks, To-Dos, Issues, Headlines</strong> (as spreadsheets) and your <strong>Scorecard</strong> (as CSV) — one team at a time, and widen the date range first.</li><li>Drag those files into the drop zone (up to 12 files).</li><li>You get a free, private preview — a \"What we found\" count and a rebuilt roster showing who owns what. Nothing is stored yet.</li><li>Click <strong>Import into my workspace</strong> to commit. (If you're not signed in, it'll prompt you to sign in, then you re-drop and re-click.) Re-running won't create duplicates.</li></ol>",
